sources.name: sUserData
sources.description: This is the description sections.  This is a parquet data source.

typeProperties.script:
source(output(
		create_date as timestamp,
		user_id as string,
		first_name as string,
		last_name as string,
		FullName as string,
		login_id as string,
		email as string,
		active as integer,
		update_date as timestamp,
		billable as integer,
		mscrm_system_user_id as integer,
		mscrm_cat_consultant_id as integer,
		mscrm_contact_id as integer,
		contractor_rate as integer,
		contractor_rate_type as integer,
		user_guid as integer,
		bamboo_id as double,
		practice as string,
		current_manager as integer,
		xCustom as string,
		joblevel_rate as integer,
		mobile_phone as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	format: 'parquet') ~> sUserData
sUserData select(mapColumn(
		create_date,
		user_id,
		first_name,
		last_name,
		FullName,
		login_id,
		email,
		active,
		update_date,
		billable,
		mscrm_system_user_id,
		mscrm_cat_consultant_id,
		mscrm_contact_id,
		contractor_rate,
		contractor_rate_type,
		user_guid,
		bamboo_id,
		practice,
		current_manager,
		xCustom,
		joblevel_rate,
		mobile_phone
	),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> SelectUserData
SelectUserData aggregate(groupBy({} = billable,
		active,
		create_date,
		user_id,
		first_name,
		last_name,
		FullName,
		login_id,
		bamboo_id,
		practice,
		current_manager,
		joblevel_rate),
	create_date = max(create_date),
		{} = ERROR_FUNCTION('')) ~> Aggregate1
